I heard you quit.

270
00:23:25,905 --> 00:23:28,405
I'm on my own now.

271
00:23:30,342 --> 00:23:33,076
I built us a house down by the river.

272
00:23:33,111 --> 00:23:36,582
Fresh water, land...

273
00:23:36,617 --> 00:23:39,020
Place where the baby can grow up.

274
00:23:40,989 --> 00:23:44,560
A good solid floor and freedom...

275
00:23:45,995 --> 00:23:48,495
A fireplace that ain't that smoky.

276
00:23:48,530 --> 00:23:49,764
Stop it.

277
00:23:49,798 --> 00:23:52,168
All our love can live there.

278
00:23:52,202 --> 00:23:53,535
Can you stop it?

279
00:23:53,569 --> 00:23:55,468
That ain't real.

280
00:23:55,503 --> 00:23:56,802
Yeah, it is.

281
00:23:56,836 --> 00:23:58,936
No, it ain't.

282
00:23:58,971 --> 00:24:02,036
And I got to pretend that that don't exist.

283
00:24:03,271 --> 00:24:05,907
Come on. Come on.

284
00:24:05,942 --> 00:24:08,406
No, I got mending to do.

285
00:24:10,142 --> 00:24:12,981
Mr. Toole would be real angry
if he knew you were here.

286
00:24:13,016 --> 00:24:15,950
You should probably go.

287
00:24:39,212 --> 00:24:42,684
How would you like to be a very rich man?

288
00:24:42,718 --> 00:24:45,585
Seen a lot of rich men
end up in shallow graves.

289
00:24:45,619 --> 00:24:49,421
When the board arrives, they will see
that I have misled the government

290
00:24:49,455 --> 00:24:51,823
on their behalf. [Sighs]

291
00:24:51,858 --> 00:24:53,492
They will move against me.

292
00:24:53,527 --> 00:24:57,498
They may even try to have me imprisoned.

293
00:24:57,532 --> 00:25:02,605
The railroad will likely fail and,
well, you'll be out of a job.

294
00:25:02,639 --> 00:25:05,008
I've been in worse spots.

295
00:25:05,042 --> 00:25:10,014
I am offering you a full partnership...

296
00:25:11,348 --> 00:25:14,148
If you will help me convince them

297
00:25:14,182 --> 00:25:16,650
that everything we have
done has been necessary.

298
00:25:25,195 --> 00:25:27,131
Now, why would they believe me?

299
00:25:27,165 --> 00:25:32,002
You are an interesting
anomaly, Mr. Bohannon.

300
00:25:32,037 --> 00:25:34,604
A gunslinger and an aristocrat.

301
00:25:34,638 --> 00:25:35,905
[Chuckles]

302
00:25:35,939 --> 00:25:38,339
Yeah, wouldn't go that
far in either direction.

303
00:25:38,374 --> 00:25:41,908
Look, I am unwell.

304
00:25:41,943 --> 00:25:44,346
I simply need you to back me up.

305
00:25:44,380 --> 00:25:47,180
What if they don't believe me?

306
00:25:47,214 --> 00:25:51,922
Well, there's a good chance that
you will share in the blame.

307
00:25:51,956 --> 00:25:53,925
And a jail cell.

308
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:56,561
From the moment you accept my offer,

309
00:25:56,596 --> 00:26:00,166
all your debts owing to me
will be forgiven.

310
00:26:05,406 --> 00:26:08,943
All my debts to you were
buried with doc whitehead.

311
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:31,667
Sign the check.

312
00:26:31,701 --> 00:26:34,604
[Sighs] I know her.

313
00:26:34,638 --> 00:26:37,841
She will not leave the railroad.

314
00:26:37,875 --> 00:26:41,280
This is the best way
for us to be rid of her.

315
00:26:41,314 --> 00:26:42,581
Is it?

316
00:26:42,615 --> 00:26:46,316
Have you done something
you Haven't told me about?

317
00:26:48,219 --> 00:26:53,019
I will do this my way if your way fails.

318
00:26:53,054 --> 00:26:55,055
Your way.

319
00:26:56,425 --> 00:27:00,528
As long as there's no mess.
Do you assure me?

320
00:27:02,530 --> 00:27:04,966
I'll sign the check...

321
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:09,238
And then her fate will be
briefly in her hands...

322
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:12,941
Before it's in mine.

323
00:27:22,288 --> 00:27:24,392
[Sighs]

324
00:27:32,873 --> 00:27:37,639
Mr. Durant has offered me a
permanent place with the railroad.

325
00:27:37,673 --> 00:27:40,974
[Chuckles] He, uh...

326
00:27:41,009 --> 00:27:43,075
He offered me a partnership.

327
00:27:43,109 --> 00:27:46,076
Then it must be your job he's offering me.

328
00:27:46,111 --> 00:27:48,278
[Horses approaching]

329
00:27:50,612 --> 00:27:52,247
Whoa, whoa.

330
00:27:52,281 --> 00:27:56,120
It's one of our horses. Shit.

331
00:28:02,195 --> 00:28:05,998
It's too dangerous
for you to be out here now.

332
00:28:16,611 --> 00:28:19,279
I've been thinking about what you said.

333
00:28:19,314 --> 00:28:23,683
About all you have
is your job... and me.

334
00:28:23,717 --> 00:28:26,820
All I have is this railroad and you.

335
00:28:26,854 --> 00:28:29,022
We can build it together.

336
00:28:29,056 --> 00:28:30,956
We already are.

337
00:28:30,990 --> 00:28:33,725
Everything...

338
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:36,230
Everything to remove the
Durants is in this ledger.

339
00:28:36,265 --> 00:28:40,034
False mileage, skimming
profits, the whole lot.

340
00:28:40,068 --> 00:28:42,339
We can do this.

341
00:28:44,511 --> 00:28:45,879
Hey, no!

342
00:28:45,913 --> 00:28:47,313
Wait!

343
00:28:47,346 --> 00:28:49,546
Burning it before Durant finds
out and has you killed.

344
00:28:49,547 --> 00:28:51,507
I guaran-damn-tee he's
already thought about it.

345
00:28:52,017 --> 00:28:54,554
How do you know?

346
00:28:55,889 --> 00:28:57,387
Like he said,

347
00:28:57,422 --> 00:29:00,558
me and him's different
sides of the same coin.

348
00:29:00,593 --> 00:29:03,793
Mr. Bohannon!

349
00:29:05,661 --> 00:29:06,593
[Grunts]

350
00:29:06,628 --> 00:29:08,661
[Horses neighing]

351
00:29:08,695 --> 00:29:11,062
What is it?

352
00:29:11,096 --> 00:29:13,328
[Horses neighing]

353
00:29:13,363 --> 00:29:15,263
It's just an Indian.

354
00:29:15,297 --> 00:29:17,031
I don't know, sir...

355
00:29:17,065 --> 00:29:18,798
[Gunshot]

356
00:29:18,833 --> 00:29:20,566
[Horse neighs]

357
00:29:24,770 --> 00:29:26,237
Mr. Bohannon!

358
00:29:26,272 --> 00:29:27,738
Bring the lantern.

359
00:29:27,772 --> 00:29:29,205
Up there?

360
00:29:43,584 --> 00:29:45,684
Shine that light over here.

361
00:29:52,588 --> 00:29:54,154
Nicked him.

362
00:29:56,725 --> 00:29:59,326
Go on back to camp with Toole.

363
00:30:00,628 --> 00:30:04,428
Lily... burn that book.

364
00:30:47,826 --> 00:30:50,229
Would you keep this for me,

365
00:30:50,263 --> 00:30:54,265
and ship it back east...

366
00:30:54,299 --> 00:30:56,969
Ship it back east if something happens?

367
00:30:58,139 --> 00:31:00,276
What kind of happen?

368
00:31:03,512 --> 00:31:07,250
In case I am killed,
Mr. Ferguson.

369
00:31:10,257 --> 00:31:12,190
Why not?

370
00:31:13,359 --> 00:31:15,428
If a white woman dies and
a black man in the stew,

371
00:31:15,462 --> 00:31:16,698
who gonna hang?

372
00:31:16,732 --> 00:31:18,998
I'm just asking you to keep it.

373
00:31:19,032 --> 00:31:20,733
And I'm just saying no.

374
00:31:20,767 --> 00:31:23,037
What have I done to offend you?

375
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:30,646
Please? Please?

376
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:34,386
Get on from here.
You on my property.

377
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:53,509
This is for Eva.

378
00:31:56,981 --> 00:31:59,316
It's beautiful.

379
00:32:03,618 --> 00:32:05,881
Give me the damn package.

380
00:32:08,452 --> 00:32:10,619
Thank you, thank you.

381
00:32:16,194 --> 00:32:17,328
[Train whistle blowing]

382
00:32:36,508 --> 00:32:39,479
What's it mean when an
Indian paints hisself white?

383
00:32:42,252 --> 00:32:44,318
Where did you see the white spirit?

384
00:32:45,453 --> 00:32:49,356
Down at the gorge.
What's it mean?

385
00:32:55,461 --> 00:32:58,263
The Sioux nation
wants everyone here to die.

386
00:32:58,297 --> 00:33:00,198
When?

387
00:33:00,232 --> 00:33:03,670
Soon.

388
00:33:04,704 --> 00:33:07,472
It'll be a blood bath.

389
00:33:09,542 --> 00:33:14,280
I don't care what happens
to anyone here... but Ruth.

390
00:33:14,314 --> 00:33:16,415
No offense taken.

391
00:33:18,317 --> 00:33:20,653
You've changed,
Mr. Bohannon.

392
00:33:20,688 --> 00:33:24,692
Yeah? I'd say it's you.
Take me out there.

393
00:33:27,997 --> 00:33:31,533
If they catch us...
They'll kill you.

394
00:33:32,936 --> 00:33:35,703
Take me out there right now.

395
00:33:57,661 --> 00:33:59,362
You wanted to see me?

396
00:34:05,907 --> 00:34:08,174
It's your take from the saloon.

397
00:34:09,443 --> 00:34:11,242
You were holding out on me.

398
00:34:11,277 --> 00:34:12,543
That's for your own good.

399
00:34:12,577 --> 00:34:15,309
Against the church...
Woman.

400
00:34:16,345 --> 00:34:19,181
Word is you've separated from her, yeah?

401
00:34:19,216 --> 00:34:21,884
Actually, we're closer than ever.

402
00:34:21,918 --> 00:34:23,784
She'll never convert to the faith.

403
00:34:23,819 --> 00:34:26,086
I'm going to convert to hers.

404
00:34:27,187 --> 00:34:29,721
Would you listen to yourself?

405
00:34:29,755 --> 00:34:31,822
She's infected your mind.

406
00:34:31,856 --> 00:34:33,490
I thought it through.

407
00:34:33,524 --> 00:34:35,059
That'd kill mum.

408
00:34:35,093 --> 00:34:37,429
You'll burn in hell, Sean.

409
00:34:37,464 --> 00:34:40,828
You're forever cast in the lake of fire.

410
00:34:40,862 --> 00:34:42,296
Children's catechism.

411
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:44,265
It's in the Bible.

412
00:34:44,300 --> 00:34:46,699
I came to America to build

413
00:34:46,734 --> 00:34:50,301
a life in this world, not the next.

414
00:34:50,335 --> 00:34:54,642
Then I'll have to disown you.

415
00:34:59,077 --> 00:35:01,280
Whew.

416
00:35:02,985 --> 00:35:05,421
Do you know who I am?

417
00:35:07,254 --> 00:35:09,288
Your Elam's friend.

418
00:35:09,322 --> 00:35:10,825
I'm his brother.

419
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:13,127
I'd be that baby's Uncle.

420
00:35:14,528 --> 00:35:17,260
I appreciate your thoughts,

421
00:35:17,295 --> 00:35:20,227
but I'm Mrs. Toole
and this is his baby.

422
00:35:20,262 --> 00:35:22,030
If that how you see it,

423
00:35:22,065 --> 00:35:23,901
then you need to talk to Elam,

424
00:35:23,935 --> 00:35:26,340
'cause his heart is tearing all apart.

425
00:35:47,297 --> 00:35:50,197
It isn't time for the gathering of tribes.

426
00:35:50,232 --> 00:35:51,935
A blood moon is coming.

427
00:35:51,970 --> 00:35:53,836
What's a blood moon?

428
00:35:53,871 --> 00:35:57,139
It's a time for bloodletting...

429
00:35:57,173 --> 00:35:58,874
The settling of scores.

430
00:35:58,908 --> 00:36:01,177
Between who?
The tribes?

431
00:36:01,211 --> 00:36:03,880
They will come against you.

432
00:36:09,822 --> 00:36:11,922
[Yelling in background]

433
00:36:21,228 --> 00:36:23,828
I want you to come and tell Durant,

434
00:36:23,863 --> 00:36:26,630
so he don't think I'm crazy.

435
00:36:28,031 --> 00:36:31,369
You'll never see me again.

436
00:36:36,876 --> 00:36:41,310
What did you do after you
discovered the Sioux threat?

437
00:36:44,079 --> 00:36:47,583
Telegraphed the fort
and asked for soldiers.

438
00:36:47,617 --> 00:36:49,916
We sent men and weapons.

439
00:36:49,950 --> 00:36:54,685
Yeah, five recruits and a small cannon.
Much obliged.

440
00:37:02,161 --> 00:37:06,867
Baptism is a sacramental
cleansing of a life.

441
00:37:06,902 --> 00:37:09,036
Do you understand that?

442
00:37:09,070 --> 00:37:11,905
Of course.

443
00:37:19,214 --> 00:37:24,285
You affirm your love
of God above all things.

444
00:37:24,319 --> 00:37:27,016
All people.

445
00:37:28,617 --> 00:37:30,450
God should be so lucky.

446
00:37:30,484 --> 00:37:34,650
This is serious, Sean.

447
00:37:34,684 --> 00:37:38,184
You're going to have to
renounce your faith.

448
00:37:39,451 --> 00:37:44,720
You're going to have
to give up your saloon,

449
00:37:44,755 --> 00:37:47,158
the pleasure house...
And?

450
00:37:47,192 --> 00:37:48,792
And...

451
00:37:49,826 --> 00:37:54,364
I just can't believe
you're going to do that.

452
00:37:54,398 --> 00:37:58,303
Doesn't your church compel you

453
00:37:58,337 --> 00:38:00,603
to baptize anyone who asks?

454
00:38:01,870 --> 00:38:06,107
If you are sincere, Sean.

455
00:38:06,141 --> 00:38:10,073
Does your God allow you
to deny me access to him?

456
00:38:12,478 --> 00:38:14,713
Of course not.

457
00:38:14,747 --> 00:38:16,147
Well...

458
00:38:24,261 --> 00:38:26,960
To the river then.

459
00:39:07,981 --> 00:39:09,949
Is it that ugly?

460
00:39:11,284 --> 00:39:14,886
No... it's beautiful.

461
00:39:14,921 --> 00:39:18,026
I knew you'd come around once you saw it...

462
00:39:18,060 --> 00:39:20,961
And saw that I was serious.

463
00:39:22,196 --> 00:39:24,295
I'm married, Elam.

464
00:39:24,329 --> 00:39:26,830
Don't matter out here.

465
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:35,507
No...
My husband is, um...

466
00:39:35,541 --> 00:39:39,677
He's... he's a good
provider, and, uh...

467
00:39:39,711 --> 00:39:42,882
He's gonna be a good father.

468
00:39:44,051 --> 00:39:46,320
Me, too.

469
00:39:46,355 --> 00:39:47,721
No.

470
00:39:47,755 --> 00:39:49,788
Think about it.

471
00:39:51,623 --> 00:39:54,028
No, um...

472
00:39:56,832 --> 00:40:01,636
I'll always love you, Elam, but I...

473
00:40:01,671 --> 00:40:04,707
My future is
with Mr. Toole.

474
00:40:06,677 --> 00:40:08,746
You know you don't want that.

475
00:40:08,780 --> 00:40:11,483
It doesn't matter what I want.

476
00:40:11,517 --> 00:40:13,753
It's what's best.

477
00:40:16,656 --> 00:40:18,022
Good-bye.

478
00:40:18,057 --> 00:40:19,390
Eva!

479
00:40:21,059 --> 00:40:22,762
Oh, no.

480
00:40:28,135 --> 00:40:30,772
I looked all over for ya,

481
00:40:30,806 --> 00:40:32,908
prayed to God and Christ you weren't here,

482
00:40:32,942 --> 00:40:36,009
but here you are.

483
00:40:36,910 --> 00:40:39,845
It's not... it's not
what you think.

484
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:41,814
Steady, Mr. Ferguson!

485
00:40:45,385 --> 00:40:48,189
I thought we were on our way.

486
00:40:49,192 --> 00:40:50,393
We are.

487
00:40:50,428 --> 00:40:51,964
God spared me once,

488
00:40:51,998 --> 00:40:56,435
for what...
I thought it was you.

489
00:40:56,469 --> 00:40:59,103
Now I see God is a malicious bastard,

490
00:40:59,137 --> 00:41:01,871
a streak of cruelty as wide as the sky.

491
00:41:01,906 --> 00:41:05,607
No. I came to tell him that it's
over between us, I swear it.

492
00:41:05,641 --> 00:41:07,161
I love you, Eva, and you made me think

493
00:41:07,162 --> 00:41:10,278
that you loved me
just a little bit, as well.

494
00:41:10,313 --> 00:41:11,912
I do.

495
00:41:11,947 --> 00:41:14,515
Your heart is for
this black son of a bitch!

496
00:41:14,550 --> 00:41:17,286
Don't, please.

497
00:41:19,422 --> 00:41:21,857
Please.

498
00:41:24,863 --> 00:41:27,165
Forgive me, father.

499
00:41:33,310 --> 00:41:36,012
Aah!

500
00:41:47,797 --> 00:41:49,766
Elam!

501
00:42:23,819 --> 00:42:25,153
I'm so sorry.

502
00:42:25,187 --> 00:42:27,261
Thank you.

503
00:42:31,027 --> 00:42:33,561
[Coins dropping]

504
00:42:33,595 --> 00:42:37,868
Do you renounce the spiritual
forces of wickedness,

505
00:42:37,902 --> 00:42:41,204
reject the evil powers of this world,

506
00:42:41,238 --> 00:42:43,805
and repent of your sin?

507
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:46,910
I do.

508
00:42:46,944 --> 00:42:49,682
Do you accept the freedom and power

509
00:42:49,716 --> 00:42:53,051
God gives you to resist evil

510
00:42:53,085 --> 00:42:56,992
and oppression in whatever
forms they present themselves?

511
00:42:57,027 --> 00:42:59,397
I do.

512
00:43:00,499 --> 00:43:04,068
Do you confess Jesus Christ as your savior

513
00:43:04,103 --> 00:43:08,941
and promise to serve him as your lord?

514
00:43:08,975 --> 00:43:11,211
I do.

515
00:43:11,245 --> 00:43:13,181
Wherever
Mr. Gregory Toole is...

516
00:43:13,215 --> 00:43:17,216
I'm sure he wishes he hadn't...

517
00:43:17,250 --> 00:43:19,750
He hadn't done what he did.

518
00:43:21,386 --> 00:43:26,186
It's the nature of this place, isn't it?

519
00:43:27,556 --> 00:43:33,295
Goes and makes ya do things
that can't be undone.

520
00:43:34,861 --> 00:43:38,266
He gave every man a square deal,

521
00:43:38,300 --> 00:43:42,269
he always bought us a fair share of rounds.

522
00:43:42,304 --> 00:43:46,104
He liked to drink...

523
00:43:48,540 --> 00:43:51,476
He loved his wife.

524
00:43:52,479 --> 00:43:56,985
Today...
Today, we bury a brother.

525
00:43:59,253 --> 00:44:05,058
Sliocht sleachta ar
shliocht bhur sleachta...

526
00:44:05,092 --> 00:44:09,926
May there be a generation of children

527
00:44:09,961 --> 00:44:14,028
on the children of your children.

528
00:44:17,033 --> 00:44:18,467
Amen.

529
00:44:25,138 --> 00:44:30,572
Jesus, accept this humble
servant into your heart.

530
00:44:30,607 --> 00:44:35,245
Be reborn in the glory of Christ.

531
00:44:53,666 --> 00:44:59,036
Brother Sean... your sins
are washed away.

532
00:44:59,070 --> 00:45:01,590
I thought the lord was going to
send the angel Gabriel himself

533
00:45:01,591 --> 00:45:02,438
to strike me blind.

534
00:45:02,472 --> 00:45:06,576
Well, thankfully, that didn't happen.

535
00:45:19,987 --> 00:45:21,355
Ohh.

536
00:45:23,224 --> 00:45:25,191
Sean.

537
00:45:27,894 --> 00:45:30,164
Sean, stop!

538
00:45:44,645 --> 00:45:47,346
Good day, Mr. Durant.

539
00:45:47,381 --> 00:45:50,988
I thought we had
an agreement, Mr. Ferguson.

540
00:45:52,557 --> 00:45:54,356
This job you need doing...

541
00:45:54,390 --> 00:45:56,556
Cold feet, hmm?

542
00:45:56,591 --> 00:45:58,691
I would've thought...

543
00:45:58,726 --> 00:46:05,163
That you would want to keep your
land, your house, your future...

544
00:46:05,197 --> 00:46:07,730
You said after the bridge...

545
00:46:07,765 --> 00:46:10,633
The bridge is complete.

546
00:46:10,668 --> 00:46:13,235
It's time, Mr. Ferguson.

547
00:46:20,204 --> 00:46:22,902
Good boy. Good boy.

548
00:46:27,307 --> 00:46:29,742
[Train whistle blowing]

549
00:46:31,946 --> 00:46:34,211
"From major Joshua
Short, U.S. Army...

550
00:46:34,245 --> 00:46:36,542
"Dear Thomas...

551
00:46:36,577 --> 00:46:40,215
"I received your request
for military support.

552
00:46:40,249 --> 00:46:44,947
"Though I wish I could accommodate
all similar requests,

553
00:46:44,982 --> 00:46:49,283
unless your scout can provide
better intelligence..."

554
00:46:49,317 --> 00:46:53,887
"I'm afraid we can't
accommodate you at this time."

555
00:46:54,821 --> 00:46:57,488
This is some kind of bullshit.

556
00:46:57,522 --> 00:46:59,658
This is the world we live in.

557
00:46:59,693 --> 00:47:02,898
We cannot panic every time
somebody sees an Indian

558
00:47:02,932 --> 00:47:04,801
and bring the work to a halt.

559
00:47:04,835 --> 00:47:06,715
Well, guess what? The
men are already spooked.

560
00:47:06,716 --> 00:47:09,038
Damn it!
Thomas...

561
00:47:10,839 --> 00:47:12,840
What will you need?

562
00:47:12,875 --> 00:47:15,211
To keep them working?

563
00:47:23,188 --> 00:47:25,056
[Footsteps]

564
00:47:26,158 --> 00:47:27,792
Cullen?

565
00:47:33,066 --> 00:47:35,402
Mr. Ferguson.

566
00:47:38,638 --> 00:47:41,840
Sit down.

567
00:47:47,481 --> 00:47:50,949
Did you change your mind about sending it?

568
00:47:50,983 --> 00:47:54,215
In case something happen to you?

569
00:47:54,250 --> 00:47:55,817
Mr. Durant have it his way,

570
00:47:55,851 --> 00:47:58,687
I'm gonna be shipping it in the morning.

571
00:48:05,096 --> 00:48:08,098
You're here to kill me.

572
00:48:09,667 --> 00:48:12,939
Mr. Durant
promised me my land

573
00:48:12,973 --> 00:48:15,073
and my house down on the river.

574
00:48:22,583 --> 00:48:26,689
My life is worth only a few
acres of river bottom.

575
00:48:26,724 --> 00:48:28,924
It's a nice spot.

576
00:48:31,594 --> 00:48:33,895
How are you going to do it?

577
00:48:33,929 --> 00:48:36,396
Strangle or cut.

578
00:48:38,730 --> 00:48:41,062
Probably cut.

579
00:48:56,846 --> 00:48:59,579
You got a reason for me not to?

580
00:49:00,681 --> 00:49:02,115
I don't think you're the person

581
00:49:02,150 --> 00:49:03,851
the Durants think you are.

582
00:49:03,886 --> 00:49:06,720
I done my share of killing.

583
00:49:07,989 --> 00:49:10,690
Not like this.

584
00:49:26,937 --> 00:49:29,972
How would you like to be chief of security

585
00:49:30,007 --> 00:49:31,842
operations on this railroad?

586
00:49:31,876 --> 00:49:34,178
Cullen Bohannon already that.

587
00:49:34,212 --> 00:49:35,815
Upon the arrest of the Durants,

588
00:49:35,849 --> 00:49:39,320
Mr. Bohannon and I will be
his natural replacements.

589
00:49:39,354 --> 00:49:41,489
How the Durants arrested?

590
00:49:41,524 --> 00:49:46,131
Once that package reaches its destination,

591
00:49:46,166 --> 00:49:49,567
there'll be a warrant
issued for Mr. Durant.

592
00:49:49,601 --> 00:49:56,073
For you, a permanent position
of respect on this railroad.

593
00:49:59,713 --> 00:50:02,813
Do we have a deal?

594
00:50:33,036 --> 00:50:34,698
What is it?

595
00:50:34,864 --> 00:50:36,037
Is it Indian?

596
00:50:36,072 --> 00:50:37,739
No, ma'am...

597
00:50:40,009 --> 00:50:42,177
Mr. Gunderson?

598
00:50:42,945 --> 00:50:44,613
[Crying]

599
00:51:13,009 --> 00:51:16,480
Mr. Ferguson
came to see me last night.

600
00:51:17,483 --> 00:51:19,616
Ah.

601
00:51:20,752 --> 00:51:25,524
Well, you had your chance, Lily.

602
00:51:25,558 --> 00:51:28,730
We asked you to leave town nicely.

603
00:51:32,234 --> 00:51:34,903
I told you already, Thomas.

604
00:51:34,938 --> 00:51:36,741
I won't be pushed out.

605
00:51:36,775 --> 00:51:38,644
[Chuckles]

606
00:51:38,679 --> 00:51:43,316
You betrayed me to Bohannon
over pillow talk.

607
00:51:43,351 --> 00:51:47,720
So you decided to have me killed.

608
00:51:47,754 --> 00:51:49,756
It's vulgar, Thomas.

609
00:51:49,790 --> 00:51:51,091
Sordid.

610
00:51:51,126 --> 00:51:52,326
The railroad is at stake!

611
00:51:52,361 --> 00:51:54,595
The railroad.
The railroad?

612
00:51:54,629 --> 00:51:57,968
I have borne every privation
for this railroad!

613
00:51:58,002 --> 00:52:00,706
I lost my husband, killed
another human being,

614
00:52:00,740 --> 00:52:04,175
suffered humiliation at
the hands of your wife...

615
00:52:04,210 --> 00:52:06,245
I've even endured your bed!

616
00:52:06,279 --> 00:52:10,617
That, Lily, makes you a whore.

617
00:52:12,053 --> 00:52:15,656
[Sighs] Know then that
when your precious railroad

618
00:52:15,691 --> 00:52:18,025
is ripped from your thick
and grasping fingers

619
00:52:18,059 --> 00:52:19,827
that you've been undone by a whore.

620
00:52:19,861 --> 00:52:21,696
Why?

621
00:52:23,599 --> 00:52:25,267
What have you done?

622
00:52:26,503 --> 00:52:30,670
I'll leave you to your work.

623
00:52:33,676 --> 00:52:37,244
When I try to convince them

624
00:52:37,278 --> 00:52:41,448
I was their white spirit...

625
00:52:41,482 --> 00:52:44,957
They stretched me on the ground

626
00:52:44,991 --> 00:52:50,059
and they built small fires upon my body.

627
00:52:50,094 --> 00:52:53,992
[Screaming and laughing]

628
00:52:54,026 --> 00:52:55,662
[Groaning]

629
00:52:55,696 --> 00:52:57,767
The pain must be awful.

630
00:52:57,801 --> 00:52:59,067
No!

631
00:52:59,101 --> 00:53:03,872
I should never have turned
to the... the heathens.

632
00:53:03,906 --> 00:53:07,580
You should never have lost
your place in this town.

633
00:53:09,417 --> 00:53:14,756
I have...
I have missed you...

634
00:53:14,790 --> 00:53:18,789
Seeing you by your husband's side.

635
00:53:18,824 --> 00:53:20,556
Shh.

636
00:53:20,591 --> 00:53:22,057
I'm here now.

637
00:53:22,091 --> 00:53:25,994
[Muttering] You must leave this place.

638
00:53:26,028 --> 00:53:28,531
[Cocks gun] Wait!

639
00:53:28,566 --> 00:53:31,068
Why? Why must I leave, Mr. Gunderson?

640
00:53:31,103 --> 00:53:32,871
[Grunting]

641
00:53:32,905 --> 00:53:39,579
The Sioux are attacking on the blood moon.

642
00:53:39,613 --> 00:53:42,583
Yeah. When's
that going to be?

643
00:53:43,853 --> 00:53:45,986
Tomorrow night.

644
00:53:46,021 --> 00:53:48,555
Oh, God!

645
00:53:57,730 --> 00:54:00,667
There's no need for
that, Mr. Bohannon.

646
00:54:00,701 --> 00:54:02,269
Look at him.

647
00:54:02,303 --> 00:54:04,463
I doubt he's even going to
make it through the night.

648
00:54:04,464 --> 00:54:06,237
Friend of yours or not,

649
00:54:06,271 --> 00:54:08,339
he's going to hang for
sabotaging the railroad.

650
00:54:08,374 --> 00:54:09,908
I'm putting a guard on him.

651
00:54:11,044 --> 00:54:13,247
Hey, you!

652
00:54:13,281 --> 00:54:15,049
[Groaning]

653
00:54:15,083 --> 00:54:17,150
[Grunting]

654
00:54:29,794 --> 00:54:31,664
Stop! This is not the way.

655
00:54:31,698 --> 00:54:33,018
Son of a bitch tried to kill you?

656
00:54:33,019 --> 00:54:34,166
Stop!

657
00:54:34,201 --> 00:54:35,833
Stop!

658
00:54:35,868 --> 00:54:37,836
You will not kill another man in a rage,

659
00:54:37,870 --> 00:54:39,705
I won't have Durant's blood on my hands.

660
00:54:39,739 --> 00:54:41,099
Then why the hell did you tell me?

661
00:54:41,100 --> 00:54:44,372
To prove to you finally that he has to go.

662
00:54:44,407 --> 00:54:47,713
But not this way.

663
00:54:47,747 --> 00:54:50,847
You and I can build this railroad together.

664
00:54:50,882 --> 00:54:53,685
I've already shipped the ledger.

665
00:54:53,719 --> 00:54:56,421
But the board won't take a woman seriously.

666
00:54:56,455 --> 00:54:58,790
I can't do this without you.

667
00:55:03,227 --> 00:55:06,629
And you...

668
00:55:07,931 --> 00:55:13,401
You're better with me, aren't you?

669
00:55:15,834 --> 00:55:17,201
Yeah.

670
00:55:18,403 --> 00:55:20,705
I am.

671
00:55:23,211 --> 00:55:27,446
I want you on the first
railcar out of here.

672
00:55:27,480 --> 00:55:29,580
You ain't gonna be on it, is you?

673
00:55:29,614 --> 00:55:30,950
No.

674
00:55:30,984 --> 00:55:33,116
Thought so.

675
00:55:35,084 --> 00:55:36,882
Protect our bridge.

676
00:55:36,917 --> 00:55:41,089
I'll be here waiting for
you when you get back.

677
00:56:05,449 --> 00:56:07,181
You know how to work a Cannon?

678
00:56:07,215 --> 00:56:09,285
Cannon?

679
00:56:09,319 --> 00:56:11,721
I seen plenty Cannon work.

680
00:56:11,756 --> 00:56:14,591
You really got one?

681
00:56:14,625 --> 00:56:17,896
Mount up, this ain't no place to die.

682
00:56:25,405 --> 00:56:27,840
Thanks for not killin' my lady friend.

683
00:56:27,874 --> 00:56:29,508
You welcome.

684
00:56:29,543 --> 00:56:31,377
Gotta ask you though.

685
00:56:31,411 --> 00:56:33,947
Was you ever gonna do it?

686
00:56:33,981 --> 00:56:36,249
You know your Bible?

687
00:56:36,284 --> 00:56:39,184
Some.

688
00:56:39,218 --> 00:56:41,317
You know when the angel came down,

689
00:56:41,351 --> 00:56:45,420
grab a hold of Abraham's arm right
before he cut Isaac's neck?

690
00:56:45,454 --> 00:56:46,788
Yeah?

691
00:56:46,822 --> 00:56:48,657
It won't like that.

692
00:56:48,692 --> 00:56:52,394
Almost got my ass shot.

693
00:56:53,729 --> 00:56:56,863
She ain't a woman to be messed with.

694
00:56:56,898 --> 00:56:58,565
True.

695
00:56:58,599 --> 00:57:00,032
True, she ain't.

696
00:57:00,066 --> 00:57:02,601
Hmm. Let's do it.

697
00:57:02,636 --> 00:57:04,736
[Clicking]

698
00:57:04,771 --> 00:57:05,756
Ahh.

699
00:57:26,817 --> 00:57:30,286
If I could have a quiet word, please.

700
00:57:32,023 --> 00:57:34,493
[Gasping]

701
00:57:53,850 --> 00:57:59,123
My personal ledgers...
How damning are they?

702
00:57:59,157 --> 00:58:05,466
You ask because you have lost them, hmm?

703
00:58:05,500 --> 00:58:08,069
How damning?

704
00:58:08,103 --> 00:58:13,611
How far you are falling, min herrdome.

705
00:58:13,646 --> 00:58:21,250
You may fall through
the floor into hell itself.

706
00:58:21,284 --> 00:58:23,318
[Gasping]

707
00:58:23,353 --> 00:58:30,128
At least a prison in upstate New York.

708
00:58:30,163 --> 00:58:33,866
What am I going to do?

709
00:58:33,900 --> 00:58:40,332
You are suffering...
That is good!

710
00:58:40,367 --> 00:58:44,738
Suffering builds character.

711
00:58:44,773 --> 00:58:50,109
You will need that during
your incarceration.

712
00:58:50,143 --> 00:58:51,478
I will die in prison.

713
00:58:51,513 --> 00:58:56,949
[Gasping] That is not true.

714
00:58:56,984 --> 00:59:00,722
Come... come.

715
00:59:00,756 --> 00:59:03,324
The truth is...

716
00:59:03,358 --> 00:59:07,961
You will not die in prison but here.

717
00:59:07,995 --> 00:59:14,867
Soon, in the streets of hell on wheels...

718
00:59:14,901 --> 00:59:16,101
[Gasping]

719
00:59:16,136 --> 00:59:21,845
Come. Let me
kiss you farewell.

720
00:59:21,879 --> 00:59:24,448
Get your filthy hands off me!

721
00:59:24,483 --> 00:59:26,584
[Screaming]

722
00:59:29,290 --> 00:59:31,293
[Gasping]

723
00:59:35,799 --> 00:59:39,470
Was Durant aware of the impending attack?

724
00:59:39,504 --> 00:59:45,111
We did what we could...

725
00:59:45,146 --> 00:59:48,083
Evacuated the women and
children, and we armed the rest.

726
00:59:48,117 --> 00:59:50,086
Did Mr. Durant
attempt to flee?

727
00:59:50,120 --> 00:59:52,958
At least not with the women and children.

728
00:59:52,992 --> 00:59:54,227
Where is Durant?

729
00:59:54,262 --> 00:59:56,594
In custody.

730
01:00:00,165 --> 01:00:01,898
[Chatter]

731
01:00:01,932 --> 01:00:03,132
[Train whistle blowing]

732
01:00:04,833 --> 01:00:07,665
God be with you.
And with you.

733
01:00:07,699 --> 01:00:09,835
[Indistinct]

734
01:00:11,471 --> 01:00:13,807
Excuse me.

735
01:00:13,841 --> 01:00:17,241
[Bell clanging]

736
01:00:17,275 --> 01:00:18,843
All right.
Here we go.

737
01:00:19,845 --> 01:00:22,215
Excuse me.

738
01:00:22,250 --> 01:00:25,650
There'll be another train
in the... in the evening.

739
01:00:25,684 --> 01:00:27,686
Please.
Everybody... stand back.

740
01:00:27,721 --> 01:00:28,989
There's room for everyone.

741
01:00:29,023 --> 01:00:30,924
Be careful.
You all right?

742
01:00:30,959 --> 01:00:32,893
All right.
Form a single line.

743
01:00:32,928 --> 01:00:34,192
One at a time.

744
01:00:34,227 --> 01:00:35,928
[Overlapping chatter]

745
01:00:38,834 --> 01:00:40,266
Let me help you.

746
01:00:40,300 --> 01:00:41,867
Are you leaving?

747
01:00:41,901 --> 01:00:43,936
Heading for council bluffs?

748
01:00:43,970 --> 01:00:45,939
Don't tell me you can't recognize

749
01:00:45,974 --> 01:00:47,343
your own travel case, Ruth.

750
01:00:47,378 --> 01:00:50,883
You packed my things?

751
01:00:50,918 --> 01:00:52,151
Why?

752
01:00:52,185 --> 01:00:53,519
As you said...

753
01:00:53,553 --> 01:00:55,754
I'm going to council bluffs.

754
01:00:55,789 --> 01:00:58,291
You're coming with me.

755
01:00:59,426 --> 01:01:03,500
My place is here.
My church.

756
01:01:03,535 --> 01:01:10,106
I have taken the liberty
of wiring the mission.

757
01:01:10,140 --> 01:01:14,977
We can be wed tomorrow noon.

758
01:01:15,011 --> 01:01:16,811
Sean, I can't.

759
01:01:16,845 --> 01:01:20,144
I have removed every obstacle.

760
01:01:20,179 --> 01:01:23,215
I have done everything you've wanted.

761
01:01:23,250 --> 01:01:28,354
And I have already given you my answer.

762
01:01:28,389 --> 01:01:30,357
I'm not ready, Sean.

763
01:01:30,392 --> 01:01:32,658
I'm sorry.

764
01:01:32,692 --> 01:01:34,160
[Train whistle blowing]

765
01:01:47,906 --> 01:01:50,105
This here our ordnance?

766
01:01:50,140 --> 01:01:51,742
Can you tell me who's in charge?

767
01:01:51,776 --> 01:01:53,078
You're lookin' at him.

768
01:01:53,112 --> 01:01:56,180
Let's see what you got.

769
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:04,653
Whoo! [Laughing]

770
01:02:04,688 --> 01:02:06,823
Now, that's the kinda sugar papa likes!

771
01:02:06,857 --> 01:02:08,490
Mm-hmm.

772
01:02:20,199 --> 01:02:22,035
Why you ain't on that damn train?

773
01:02:22,069 --> 01:02:23,236
I ain't runnin'.

774
01:02:23,271 --> 01:02:24,431
If Bohannon can't hold 'em...

775
01:02:24,438 --> 01:02:25,838
I'm goin' to your house.

776
01:02:25,872 --> 01:02:27,172
My house?

777
01:02:27,206 --> 01:02:31,178
This ain't
about you and me. I...

778
01:02:31,213 --> 01:02:33,782
It's the safest place
to wait out the Sioux.

779
01:02:33,817 --> 01:02:35,184
What about after the Sioux?

780
01:02:35,220 --> 01:02:39,322
I don't know.

781
01:02:39,356 --> 01:02:43,559
I... I got blood
on my hands, Elam.

782
01:02:43,594 --> 01:02:46,532
It's bad magic and you don't
need to be a part of it.

783
01:02:46,567 --> 01:02:50,068
Listen here...
Mr. Toole ain't on you.

784
01:02:50,102 --> 01:02:51,870
He took the coward way out.

785
01:02:51,904 --> 01:02:57,211
No, he didn't. No, every man's
got his limits, Elam. And...

786
01:02:57,245 --> 01:02:59,277
He didn't deserve what he got.

787
01:02:59,312 --> 01:03:01,313
No, none of us deserve it.

788
01:03:01,347 --> 01:03:04,017
Did you deserve the hardships you got?

789
01:03:04,052 --> 01:03:06,451
Did you ever think to do like he did?

790
01:03:06,485 --> 01:03:08,153
No.
No.

791
01:03:08,187 --> 01:03:09,621
'Cause you strong.

792
01:03:09,655 --> 01:03:12,056
And that baby gonna be strong.

793
01:03:12,091 --> 01:03:13,693
Let's get to that house.

794
01:03:13,727 --> 01:03:15,328
I know the way.

795
01:03:15,362 --> 01:03:17,402
There weren't no room on
the train for the whores.

796
01:03:17,403 --> 01:03:18,896
I'd be obliged if you kept 'em safe.

797
01:03:18,930 --> 01:03:21,063
[Train whistle blowing]

798
01:03:21,097 --> 01:03:23,498
[Flies buzzing]

799
01:03:31,539 --> 01:03:32,806
Finish our game?

800
01:03:32,840 --> 01:03:34,841
Rest.

801
01:03:34,875 --> 01:03:36,309
I...

802
01:03:36,343 --> 01:03:38,346
Must have rest.

803
01:03:38,380 --> 01:03:43,149
[Groaning] Rest.

804
01:03:47,854 --> 01:03:49,823
[Grunting]

805
01:04:16,119 --> 01:04:17,788
[Gasps]

806
01:04:18,790 --> 01:04:19,858
You ok?

807
01:04:19,892 --> 01:04:22,761
Rest!

808
01:05:07,140 --> 01:05:09,240
[Grunting]

809
01:05:14,077 --> 01:05:18,549
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

810
01:05:18,584 --> 01:05:22,190
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

811
01:05:45,450 --> 01:05:46,619
